load ../infoflow-package.maude

--- Coverage: a package that ran the IFC check is attested, and a cross-package
--- grant whose surface fits the consumer envelope is accepted.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-PACKAGE :
  ifcChecked(t1) grants(t1) surfaceFits(t1)
  =>* C:Cfg accepted(t1) .

--- Coverage: a grant whose declared surface exceeds the envelope is rejected.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-PACKAGE :
  grants(t1) surfaceExceeds(t1)
  =>* C:Cfg rejected(t1) .

--- Coverage: a grant to a package with no IFC attestation is rejected.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-PACKAGE :
  grants(t1) notIfcAttested(t1)
  =>* C:Cfg rejected(t1) .

--- Bite: no attestation, no acceptance. A package the producer never IFC-attested
--- is never accepted across the boundary. The RESIDUAL soup var makes any accepted
--- state a solution, so No solution proves it.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-PACKAGE :
  grants(t1) notIfcAttested(t1)
  =>* accepted(t1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the consumer-side surface gate holds. Even an IFC-attested package whose
--- declared surface EXCEEDS the consumer envelope is never accepted -- the producer
--- attestation alone does not grant; the surface must fit the envelope (X8).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-PACKAGE :
  grants(t1) attestsIfc(t1) surfaceExceeds(t1)
  =>* accepted(t1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
